Membership
Membership
Apply online via the form on this page or print and submit a written application with payment to:
Stage West Playhouse
8390 Forest Oaks Blvd.
Spring Hill, Fl. 34606
Questions call: 352-683-5114
Print Application
Please help us support the arts local artists in our community. Become a member of Stage West Productions and enjoy the benefits.
General Meetings are held at 7:30 p.m. on the 2nd Wednesday of June, Aug., Oct., Dec., Feb., and Apr. Board of Directors meet the last Wednesday of each month at 7:00 p.m. Meetings are open to the public and offer an opportunity for public comment.
Stage West is a registered 501(c) (3) nonprofit community organization dedicated to promoting the theater arts.

Anyone needing financial assistance may contact any board member to submit a request. A “Family” is defined as the adults and their children age 17 and younger living in the same household.
Membership Agreement
(Required)
I consent to the membership agreement.
Membership meetings are held at the theater the 2nd Wednesday of EVERY month (starting in June) at 7:30 pm. After you submit your membership form, please meet with the Membership Chairperson to receive your card and submit your dues. You will not become an Active Member until your dues are recorded and all other requirements (as stated in the By-Laws) are fulfilled. Each member is required to volunteer a minimum number of hours each year, as set forth by the Board of Directors, as well as attend a minimum of six (6) Membership meetings each year to be eligible to vote or hold a position on the Board of Directors.
•	I HEREBY STATE THAT I HAVE READ THE FOREGOING AND AGREE TO THE TERMS OF MEMBERSHIP AS STATED HEREIN, AS WELL AS TO THE BY-LAWS, ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION, AND THE POLICIES OF STAGE WEST.
•	I UNDERSTAND THAT FAILURE TO MEET MEMBERSHIP REQUIREMENTS WILL FORFIET MY VOTING RIGHTS AS A MEMBER.

(Required)

About Stage West
Stage West is a registered 501(c) (3) nonprofit community organization dedicated to promoting the theater arts.

About Us
MISSION STATEMENT
Stage West Playhouse is a non-profit community organization dedicated to promoting the theatre arts in the tri-county area and beyond.
PURPOSE
This corporation is organized for educational, cultural, and other non-profit purposes pursuant to section 501 (c)(3) Internal Revenue Code.
Stage West is committed to increasing community interest in the performing arts, providing educational and recreational opportunities and in creating an organizational environment which encourages the participation of community members from all age groups and interest levels.
DESCRIPTION
Stage West Playhouse is a amateur theatre company operating as Hernando County Florida’s oldest ocmmunity theater. For over 40 yearss State West has provided the residents of Hernando. Pasco and Citrus counties quality theatrical entertainment at an affordable price.
Our main stage production portfolio over the years is an impressive display of some of the best known and most beloved shows of all time. From the King and I, Camelot, 1776. A Few Good Men, One Flew Over the Cuckoo’s Nest and the Wizard of Oz. Stage West is a staple of the Tampa Bay Area.
Board of Directors
President- Theresa Stenger
Vice President – Paul Wade
Treasurer – Sandy Penwarden
Secretary – Ellen Hutt
Business and Policy – Linda Willding
Marketing Director – Michelle Root
Facilities – Bob Cree
Hospitality – Linda Hougland
Executive Producer – Ed Francis
Artistic Director – Char Adams
